They are empty in timestepSetup() in the interface, at that point it's just an insertion point, but you can override them and place what you want "done at the beginning of every time step" in those routines.
Maybe start by adding this to your class:
void
MyReader::timestepSetup()
{
  _console << "Going to setup here" << std::endl;
}

and see if it gets triggered at the moments desired

